solution: ```class Solution {
    public int minSteps(int n) {
        if (n == 1) return 0;
        int res = 0;
        for (int d = 2; d <= n; d++) {
            while (n % d == 0) {
                res += d;
                n /= d;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Decompose n into its prime factors; the sum of these factors equals the minimal operations. Each factor represents a copy followed by (factor-1) pastes.

